                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17568" author="bayard" created="Fri, 12 May 2006 02:57:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A similar issue: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://opensource.atlassian.com/projects/spring/browse/SPR-2002&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://opensource.atlassian.com/projects/spring/browse/SPR-2002&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18066" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 19 Jun 2006 08:02:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, I tend to agree that it&apos;s a bit unintuitive, but... why wouldn&apos;t you simply use request.getParameter if all you want is straight raw access to the parameter String? The ServletRequestUtils.getStringParameter variants are really only meant as direct equivalent of the typed accessors for numbers and booleans, for Strings that either have to be non-empty or not exist at all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18098" author="yatesco" created="Mon, 19 Jun 2006 20:36:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Juergen; I think there are two points:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;mixing both request.getParameter and RequestUtils.getStringParameter is less than ideal; it would be nice if there was a single entry point.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;required*Parameter* is also a bit misleading....you are not insisting that the &lt;b&gt;parameter&lt;/b&gt; is specified, rather you are insisting that the &lt;b&gt;value&lt;/b&gt; is specified.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Maybe the methods should be renamed RequestUtils.getRequiredXXXValue() and getOptionalXXXValue(), where the optional operations never throw an exception (unless the data conversion fails).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just a thought, and not a particularly well thought one at that &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18981" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 9 Aug 2006 23:40:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have changed the behavior to treat empty values as valid for Strings (&quot;&quot;) and booleans (false). I&apos;ve only changed this for ServletRequestUtils and PortletRequestUtils, though; the deprecated RequestUtils remains backwards-compatible with 1.2 in that it still follows the former rules.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
